            <section class="abstract">
                <h2>Abstract</h2>
                <p>This initiative proposes the integration of Artificial Intelligence (AI) and Machine Learning (ML) fundamentals into the core undergraduate curriculum across all engineering disciplines. The goal is to equip students with the necessary skills to navigate an AI-driven job market. This includes the development of two new mandatory courses and the revision of three existing courses to include AI-assisted problem-solving modules.</p>
            </section>

            <section class="detailed-proposal">
                <h2>Detailed Proposal</h2>
                <p>The rapid advancement of AI technologies necessitates a shift in how we approach engineering education. Currently, AI topics are relegated to elective courses, often missing a large portion of the student body. This initiative aims to democratize AI knowledge.</p>

                <h3>Key Objectives:</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Design a “Foundations of AI” course for Freshmen.</li>
                    <li>Integrate AI tools (e.g., Python libraries, generative design) into Capstone projects.</li>
                    <li>Train faculty members on AI ethics and application.</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Expected Outcomes:</h3>
                <p>We anticipate a 40% increase in student engagement in research projects involving ML and a higher employability rate for graduates in tech-forward sectors.</p>
            </section>

